The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 December is 1,937,598 (3,442.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 December, there were 211,040 new confirmed cases (374.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 December, there were 136,225 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 55% (74,815 extra cases).
